Steps to flash AQ firmware for AQ PHY on u-boot
-----------------------------------------------

Required input images:
---------------------
Software to programm PHY firmware
  File Name:aq_programming.bin
PHY firmware

LX2160A-RDB boards
------------------
AQR107(XFI):
        AQR-G2_v3.5.E-AQR_Freescale_LX2RDB-USXGMII_ID24109_VER965.cld
AQR107(USXGMII):
        AQR-G2_v3.5.E-AQR_Freescale_LX2RDB-USXGMII_ID24109_VER965.cld

LX2160A-QDS boards
------------------	
AQR405(XFI):
        AQR405:AQ28nm_v2.C.8-AQR_Freescale_LX2QDS-XFI_ID24724_VER1019.cld
AQR405(USXGMII):
        AQR405:AQ28nm_v2.C.8-AQR_Freescale_LX2QDS-USXGMII_ID24191_VER997.cld


T2080-xxx boards
----------------
AQ1202:
        Firmware_1.37.10_011014_Freescale_T2080PCIe.cld

T1024-RDB boards
----------------
AQR105(2.5G SGMII):
        AQ28nm-FW_2.0.B3_Freescale_T1024RDB_120514.cld
AQR105(10G XFI):
        AQ28nm-FW_2.0.B9_Freescale_T1024RDB_012115.cld

Steps to flash firmware on RDB board
------------------------------------
1. Download above mentioned Aquantia PHY firmware and the firmware update
   utility (aq_programming.bin) to tftp location or storage media.

2. Check MACs connected to an Aquantia PHY (LX2160A-RDB example)
   => mdio list
   FSL_MDIO0:
   0 - Cortina CS4223 <--> DPMAC2@xlaui4
   1 - AR8035 <--> DPMAC17@rgmii-id
   2 - AR8035 <--> DPMAC18@rgmii-id
   4 - Aquantia AQR107 <--> DPMAC3@xgmii
   5 - Aquantia AQR107 <--> DPMAC4@xgmii

3. Execute aq_programming.bin to flash PHY firmware
   Usage: go 0x80300000 <ETHDEV_NAME> <firmware_address> <firmware_size>

   USB example:
   usb start;
   fatload usb 0:1 0x80300000 aq_programming.bin;
   fatload usb 0:1 0x82000000 AQR-G2_v3.5.E-AQR_Freescale_LX2RDB-XFI_ID24377_VER965.cld;
   go 0x80300000 DPMAC3@xgmii 0x82000000 $filesize;

   TFTP example:
   tftp 0x80300000 aq_programming.bin;
   tftp 0x82000000 AQR-G2_v3.5.E-AQR_Freescale_LX2RDB-XFI_ID24377_VER965.cld;
   go 0x80300000 DPMAC3@xgmii 0x82000000 $filesize;

4. Notes
	- Perform the update for all PHYs. In the above examples only MAC3 is
          updated, but MAC4 is also connected to an Aquantia PHY
        - For USXGMII a different firmware needs to be programmed. Steps are
          identical.

